{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f847ed2b-b35c-4f4f-a854-21ed179cb325",
    "name": "KOSMO — Auth Flow",
    "description": "Flujo de autenticación de KOSMO (OAuth 2.1 + PKCE S256, RS256, refresh-rotation).\n\n## Pre-requisitos\n\n1. Backend corriendo en `http://127.0.0.1:8000` (ver `docker-compose up` o `uv run backend`).\n2. Si quieres usar el seed user (`dev@kosmo.dev`):\n\n```\ncd backend\n.venv/Scripts/python.exe -m kosmo.infrastructure.scripts.seed_dev_user\n```\n\nSi no seedeas, la primera ejecución de **Register** crea el usuario; las siguientes devolverán 409 (esperado).\n\n## Cómo correrlo\n\nPulsa **Run collection** y ejecuta en orden:\n\n1. **Health** — sanity check\n2. **Register** — crea el usuario (idempotente: 201 o 409)\n3. **Authorize** — paso 1 del login: valida password y emite `authorization_code` (TTL 60s) atado al PKCE `code_challenge` generado en pre-request\n4. **Token** — paso 2 del login: intercambia `code` + `code_verifier` por un `TokenPair` RS256 (access + refresh)\n5. **Me** — verifica el access token y devuelve el `Principal`\n6. **Refresh** — rota el `TokenPair` (invalida el refresh anterior, emite uno nuevo en la misma `family_id`)\n7. **Logout** — revoca el access JTI y la familia entera\n\nCada test escribe sus salidas (`access_token`, `refresh_token`, `authorization_code`, etc.) **tanto en collection como en environment** (si hay uno activo). Esto evita el bug clásico en que un Environment con valores stale sombrea lo que escribe `pm.collectionVariables.set` y manda tokens viejos al siguiente request.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "32529627"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Health",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test('status=ok', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "health"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Liveness probe. Debe responder 200 con `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Register",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "function setVar(key, value) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value);",
              "    if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) {",
              "        pm.environment.set(key, value);",
              "    }",
              "}",
              "pm.test('201 (creado) o 409 (ya existe)', function () {",
              "    pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});",
              "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
              "    var body = pm.response.json();",
              "    setVar('user_id', body.id);",
              "    pm.test('email coincide', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(body.email).to.eql(pm.variables.get('email'));",
              "    });",
              "} else {",
              "    pm.test('detail = Email ya registrado', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(pm.response.json().detail).to.eql('Email ya registrado');",
              "    });",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "register"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Crea un usuario nuevo.\n\n- **201 Created** la primera vez (devuelve `UserPublic { id, email, created_at }`).\n- **409 Conflict** si el email ya existe (`detail: \"Email ya registrado\"`).\n\nValidaciones:\n- `email`: formato válido (EmailStr).\n- `password`: 12-128 caracteres."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Authorize (login paso 1)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "function setVar(key, value) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value);",
              "    if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) {",
              "        pm.environment.set(key, value);",
              "    }",
              "}",
              "function base64url(wordArray) {",
              "    return CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(wordArray)",
              "        .replace(/\\+/g, '-')",
              "        .replace(/\\//g, '_')",
              "        .replace(/=+$/, '');",
              "}",
              "// PKCE S256 — RFC 7636. Genera un par fresco en cada Authorize.",
              "var verifier = base64url(CryptoJS.lib.WordArray.random(48));",
              "var challenge = base64url(CryptoJS.SHA256(verifier));",
              "setVar('code_verifier', verifier);",
              "setVar('code_challenge', challenge);"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "function setVar(key, value) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value);",
              "    if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) {",
              "        pm.environment.set(key, value);",
              "    }",
              "}",
              "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "var body = pm.response.json();",
              "setVar('authorization_code', body.authorization_code);",
              "pm.test('authorization_code presente', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.authorization_code).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "pm.test('expires_in entre 1 y 60', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.expires_in).to.be.at.least(1);",
              "    pm.expect(body.expires_in).to.be.at.most(60);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\",\n  \"code_challenge\": \"{{code_challenge}}\",\n  \"code_challenge_method\": \"S256\",\n  \"scopes\": [\"read\"]\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/authorize",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "authorize"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Verifica la contraseña con Argon2id y emite un `authorization_code` de un solo uso (TTL 60s) atado al `code_challenge` enviado.\n\nEl pre-request **regenera** `code_verifier` + `code_challenge` (RFC 7636, S256) cada vez que se ejecuta este request, de modo que el flujo es repetible.\n\nRespuesta 201:\n```json\n{ \"authorization_code\": \"…\", \"expires_in\": 60 }\n```\n\nSi las credenciales son inválidas → 401 con `{ error: \"invalid_grant\", error_description: \"Credenciales inválidas\" }`."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Token (login paso 2)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "function setVar(key, value) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value);",
              "    if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) {",
              "        pm.environment.set(key, value);",
              "    }",
              "}",
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "var body = pm.response.json();",
              "setVar('access_token', body.access.token);",
              "setVar('refresh_token', body.refresh.token);",
              "pm.test('token_type Bearer', function () { pm.expect(body.token_type).to.eql('Bearer'); });",
              "pm.test('access.token presente', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.access.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "pm.test('refresh.token presente', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.refresh.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "pm.test('jti distintos', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.access.jti).to.not.eql(body.refresh.jti);",
              "});",
              "// Sanity: lo que el siguiente request enviará por {{access_token}} es el token recién emitido",
              "pm.test('access_token persistido sin shadow', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.variables.get('access_token')).to.eql(body.access.token);",
              "});",
              "pm.test('refresh_token persistido sin shadow', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.variables.get('refresh_token')).to.eql(body.refresh.token);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"grant_type\": \"authorization_code\",\n  \"code\": \"{{authorization_code}}\",\n  \"code_verifier\": \"{{code_verifier}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/token",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "token"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Consume el `authorization_code` (atómico, single-use), valida que `SHA256(code_verifier) == code_challenge`, y emite un `TokenPair` RS256:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"access\":  { \"token\": \"…\", \"jti\": \"…\", \"expires_at\": \"…\" },\n  \"refresh\": { \"token\": \"…\", \"jti\": \"…\", \"expires_at\": \"…\" },\n  \"token_type\": \"Bearer\"\n}\n```\n\nAmbos tokens comparten un `family_id` único por sesión.\n\nSi el `code` ya fue consumido, expiró, o el verifier no coincide → 400 `invalid_grant`."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Me",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "var body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('subject presente', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.subject).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "pm.test('scopes incluye read', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.scopes).to.include('read');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/me",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "me"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Verifica la firma RS256 del access token, comprueba que su `jti` no esté revocado y que la familia siga viva, y devuelve el `Principal`:\n\n```json\n{ \"subject\": \"<user_id>\", \"scopes\": [\"read\"] }\n```\n\nSin token → 401."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Refresh",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "function setVar(key, value) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value);",
              "    if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) {",
              "        pm.environment.set(key, value);",
              "    }",
              "}",
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "var body = pm.response.json();",
              "setVar('access_token', body.access.token);",
              "setVar('refresh_token', body.refresh.token);",
              "pm.test('nuevos tokens emitidos', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(body.access.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "    pm.expect(body.refresh.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"grant_type\": \"refresh_token\",\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/refresh",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "refresh"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Rota el `TokenPair`:\n\n- Consume el refresh actual (atomic).\n- Emite un nuevo access + refresh con el mismo `family_id`.\n- Si el refresh ya fue consumido (replay) → revoca toda la familia (RFC 6819 §5.2.2.3) y responde 401.\n\nSe sobreescriben `access_token` y `refresh_token` con los nuevos."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Logout",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('204 No Content', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(204); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          },
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/logout",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "logout"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Revoca el access JTI (hasta que expire por TTL) y la familia entera. Cualquier token de la sesión queda inservible inmediatamente. Responde **204 No Content**.\n\nTras esto, llamar a `/auth/me` con ese access devolverá 401."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "8. Rate limit — Saturar /register (→ 429)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "var url = pm.variables.get('base_url') + '/api/v1/auth/register';",
              "var body = JSON.stringify({ email: 'ratelimit-reg@kosmo.dev', password: 'dev-password-12345' });",
              "var req = { url: url, method: 'POST', header: [{ key: 'Content-Type', value: 'application/json' }], body: { mode: 'raw', raw: body } };",
              "function fill(n, done) {",
              "    if (n === 0) { done(); return; }",
              "    pm.sendRequest(req, function(err, res) { fill(n - 1, done); });",
              "}",
              "fill(3, function() {});"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('429 Too Many Requests', function() { pm.response.to.have.status(429); });",
              "pm.test('Retry-After header presente', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Retry-After')).to.match(/^[0-9]+$/);",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Mensaje en español', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().detail).to.include('Demasiadas solicitudes');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"ratelimit-reg@kosmo.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"dev-password-12345\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "register"
          ]
        },
        "description": "El pre-request script envía 3 requests previos para llenar el bucket del rate limiter (límite: 3/min por IP). Este 4° request debe recibir **429** con el header `Retry-After`.\n\n⚠️ Si ya ejecutaste este request hace menos de 60s el bucket puede haberse reseteado. Espera 60s y vuelve a ejecutar si obtienes 201/409."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "9. Rate limit — Saturar /authorize (→ 429)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "var url = pm.variables.get('base_url') + '/api/v1/auth/authorize';",
              "var body = JSON.stringify({ email: 'nobody@kosmo.dev', password: 'wrong-password-xyz', code_challenge: 'E9Melhoa2OwvFrEMTJguCHaoeK1t8URWbuGJSstw-cM', code_challenge_method: 'S256', scopes: [] });",
              "var req = { url: url, method: 'POST', header: [{ key: 'Content-Type', value: 'application/json' }], body: { mode: 'raw', raw: body } };",
              "function fill(n, done) {",
              "    if (n === 0) { done(); return; }",
              "    pm.sendRequest(req, function(err, res) { fill(n - 1, done); });",
              "}",
              "fill(10, function() {});"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('429 Too Many Requests', function() { pm.response.to.have.status(429); });",
              "pm.test('Retry-After header presente', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Retry-After')).to.match(/^[0-9]+$/);",
              "});",
              "pm.test('Mensaje en español', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().detail).to.include('Demasiadas solicitudes');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"nobody@kosmo.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"wrong-password-xyz\",\n  \"code_challenge\": \"E9Melhoa2OwvFrEMTJguCHaoeK1t8URWbuGJSstw-cM\",\n  \"code_challenge_method\": \"S256\",\n  \"scopes\": []\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/authorize",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "v1",
            "auth",
            "authorize"
          ]
        },
        "description": "El pre-request script envía 10 requests a `/authorize` con un usuario inexistente (límite: 10/min). Este 11° request supera el límite y debe recibir **429**.\n\n⚠️ Si ya ejecutaste otros requests a `/authorize` en el último minuto, el contador puede estar elevado. Espera 60s si obtienes un error inesperado."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "10. Lockout — Registrar usuario de prueba",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 (creado) o 409 (ya existe)', function() {",
              "    pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"lockout@kosmo.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"lockout-pwd-12345\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
